{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
    "chapterNumber": 1,
    "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1",
    "summary": "Source text for Song of Solomon 1 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:1",
      "text": "THE Song of songs, which is Solomon's.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:2",
      "text": "Let him kiss me with the kisses of his mouth: for thy breasts are better than wine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:3",
      "text": "And the smell of thine ointments is better than all spices: thy name is ointment poured forth; therefore do the young maidens love thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:4",
      "text": "They have drawn thee: we will run after thee, for the smell of thine ointments: the king has brought me into his closet: let us rejoice and be glad in thee; we will love thy breasts more than wine: righteousness loves thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:5",
      "text": "I am black, but beautiful, ye daughters of Jerusalem, as the tents of Kedar, as the curtains of Solomon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:6",
      "text": "Look not upon me, because I am dark, because the sun has looked unfavourably upon me: my mother's sons strove with me; they made me keeper in the vineyards; I have not kept my own vineyard.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:7",
      "text": "Tell me, thou whom my soul loves, where thou tendest thy flock, where thou causest them to rest at noon, lest I become as one that is veiled by the flocks of thy companions.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:8",
      "text": "If thou know not thyself, thou fair one among women, go thou forth by the footsteps of the flocks, and feed thy kids by the shepherds' tents.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:9",
      "text": "I have likened thee, my companion, to my horses in the chariots of Pharao.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:10",
      "text": "How are thy cheeks beautiful as those of a dove, thy neck as chains!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:11",
      "text": "We will make thee figures of gold with studs of silver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:12",
      "text": "So long as the king was at table, my spikenard gave forth its smell.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:13",
      "text": "My kinsman is to me a bundle of myrrh; he shall lie between my breasts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:14",
      "text": "My kinsman is to me a cluster of camphor in the vineyards of Engaddi.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:15",
      "text": "Behold, thou art fair, my companion; behold, thou art fair; thine eyes are doves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:16",
      "text": "Behold, thou art fair, my kinsman, yea, beautiful, overshadowing our bed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:song-of-solomon.1.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:17",
      "text": "The beams of our house are cedars, our ceilings are of cypress.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
